# Data Layer Standards

## Structure

All content lives in `lib/data/` — never in components or pages.

```
lib/
├── data/
│   ├── site-config.ts        # site name, URL, social links, default SEO
│   ├── navigation.ts         # nav links, footer links
│   ├── pages/                # one file per page
│   │   ├── home.ts
│   │   ├── about.ts
│   │   └── services.ts
│   └── content/              # reusable shared content blocks
├── types/
│   ├── seo.ts
│   ├── navigation.ts
│   └── [feature].ts
└── seo/
    └── jsonld.ts             # JSON-LD schema helpers
```

## Required SEO Shape on Every Page Data Object

```ts
// Every page data object MUST include this shape
seo: {
  metaTitle: string
  metaDescription: string
  slug: string
  keywords?: string[]
  ogImageUrl?: string
}
```

## TypeScript Interface Rules

- Define interfaces in `lib/types/` for every data structure
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards if needed
- Mirror future Sanity schema structure: nested objects, arrays, references

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — mirrors Sanity schema, typed, no any
export interface ServicePage {
  seo: SeoMeta
  hero: {
    heading: string
    subheading: string
    ctaLabel: string
    ctaHref: string
  }
  services: ServiceItem[]
}

export interface ServiceItem {
  _key: string          // Sanity array items use _key
  title: string
  description: string
  icon: string
}

// ❌ BAD — inline types, missing seo, not Sanity-ready
const data = {
  title: 'Services',
  items: [{ name: 'Thing' }]
}
```

## Data File Template

```ts
import type { ServicePage } from '@/lib/types/service'

export const servicePageData: ServicePage = {
  seo: {
    metaTitle: 'Services | Site Name',
    metaDescription: '...',
    slug: '/services',
    keywords: ['...'],
  },
  hero: { ... },
  services: [{ _key: 'svc-1', title: '...', ... }],
}
```
